# help/en/overview.ftl — FreeSynergy Community Repository help texts (English)

help-community-repo-title = FreeSynergy Community Repository

help-community-repo-body =
    The FreeSynergy Community repository is an additional Store source maintained
    by community contributors. Adding it extends your Store with packages that are
    not part of the official FreeSynergy distribution.

    What you get:
    - Additional themes and icon sets beyond the built-in three
    - Community-contributed widgets for the Desktop
    - Extra language packs for regional languages and dialects
    - Third-party service integrations (bots, bridges, apps)
    - Experimental packages not yet promoted to the main Store

    All packages in the community repository are reviewed by the FreeSynergy team
    before publication, but they may have less testing than official packages.

help-community-repo-adding-title = Adding the Repository

help-community-repo-adding-body =
    The community repository is added automatically when you install this package.
    After installation, refresh the Store to see the new packages.

    To verify the repository is active:
    - Open the Store > Settings > Repositories.
    - FreeSynergy Community should appear in the list with status "active".

    To remove the repository:
    - Open the Store > Settings > Repositories.
    - Select FreeSynergy Community and click Remove.
    - Any packages installed from this repository will remain installed but will
      no longer receive updates until the repository is re-added.

help-community-repo-contributing-title = Contributing Packages

help-community-repo-contributing-body =
    To submit a package to the community repository:
    1. Fork the fs-store-community repository on GitHub.
    2. Follow the package format documented in CONTRIBUTING.md.
    3. Open a pull request — the FreeSynergy team will review it.
    4. Once approved, the package appears in the community Store for all users.

    See the repository README for guidelines on package quality and licensing.
